	"item": [
		{
			"name": "🔌 1. Setup & Health Check",
			"description": "Verificaciones básicas de conectividad con el brain server.",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "🟢 Health Check — GET /mcp",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
									"pm.test('Body has status ok', () => {",
									"    const json = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('ok');",
									"});",
									"pm.test('Response time < 500ms', () => pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(500));"
								]
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{brain_url}}/mcp",
							"host": ["{{brain_url}}"],
							"path": ["mcp"]
						},
						"description": "Endpoint de health-check. Confirma que el servidor MCP está vivo.\n\n**Los agentes IA lo usan para verificar conectividad inicial.**"
					}
				},
				{
					"name": "🔗 SSE Connection — GET /sse",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Status 200 — SSE endpoint reachable', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
									"",
									"// Nota: Postman no maneja SSE streams completos.",
									"// Esta llamada establece la conexión y permite obtener un sessionId",
									"// del Set-Cookie o del primer evento SSE.",
									"//",
									"// Para debugging real, recomendamos:",
									"//   curl -N http://localhost:3015/sse",
									"//",
									"// O usar la extensión SSE de Postman (si está disponible).",
									"",
									"const contentType = pm.response.headers.get('content-type');",
									"pm.test('Response is SSE stream', () => {",
									"    pm.expect(contentType).to.include('text/event-stream');",
									"});"
								]
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Accept",
								"value": "text/event-stream"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{brain_url}}/sse",
							"host": ["{{brain_url}}"],
							"path": ["sse"]
						},
						"description": "### ⚠️ IMPORTANTE\n\nEste es el endpoint SSE (Server-Sent Events). Postman tiene soporte limitado para SSE.\n\n**Qué hace un agente IA aquí:**\n1. Abre una conexión SSE duradera a `GET /sse`\n2. Recibe eventos con `sessionId` y notificaciones de herramientas\n3. Usa ese `sessionId` para todas las llamadas posteriores a `POST /messages?sessionId=...`\n\n**Para debuggear con curl:**\n```bash\ncurl -N http://localhost:3015/sse\n```\nEsto mostrará los eventos SSE en tiempo real. La salida incluirá algo como:\n```\nevent: endpoint\ndata: /messages?sessionId=abc123\n```\nCopia ese `sessionId` y úsalo en las variables de Postman."
					}
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"name": "📡 2. MCP Protocol — JSON-RPC via POST /messages",
			"description": "Simula las llamadas JSON-RPC que hacen los **modelos IA** cuando ejecutan herramientas MCP.\n\n**Flujo típico de un agente:**\n1. `initialize` — Negociar protocolo\n2. `tools/list` — Obtener catálogo de herramientas\n3. `tools/call` — Ejecutar herramienta específica\n\n> ⚠️ Necesitas un `sessionId` válido de una conexión SSE activa.\n> Haz GET /sse primero y copia el sessionId en la variable.",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "📋 Initialize",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
									"",
									"const json = pm.response.json();",
									"pm.test('Response has jsonrpc and result', () => {",
									"    pm.expect(json.jsonrpc).to.eql('2.0');",
									"    pm.expect(json.result).to.exist;",
									"    pm.expect(json.result.serverInfo.name).to.eql('lallamaollama-brain');",
									"});"
								]
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"method\": \"initialize\",\n    \"params\": {\n        \"protocolVersion\": \"2024-11-05\",\n        \"capabilities\": {},\n        \"clientInfo\": {\n            \"name\": \"Postman Debug Client\",\n            \"version\": \"1.0.0\"\n        }\n    }\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{brain_url}}/messages?sessionId={{session_id}}",
							"host": ["{{brain_url}}"],
							"path": ["messages"],
							"query": [
								{
									"key": "sessionId",
									"value": "{{session_id}}"
								}
							]
						},
						"description": "Primera llamada JSON-RPC que hace un agente IA al conectar.\nNegocia la versión del protocolo MCP y se presenta con su nombre."
					}
				},
				{
					"name": "📋 ListTools — Ver catálogo completo",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
									"",
									"const json = pm.response.json();",
									"pm.test('Has tools array', () => {",
									"    pm.expect(json.result.tools).to.be.an('array');",
									"});",
									"",
									"const tools = json.result.tools;",
									"const toolNames = tools.map(t => t.name);",
									"",
									"pm.test('Has mem_save', () => pm.expect(toolNames).to.include('mem_save'));",
									"pm.test('Has mem_my_compliance', () => pm.expect(toolNames).to.include('mem_my_compliance'));",
									"pm.test('All tools have agent field', () => {",
									"    const allHaveAgent = tools.every(t => t.inputSchema.properties.agent);",
									"    pm.expect(allHaveAgent).to.be.true;",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test(`Found ${tools.length} tools`, () => {",
									"    pm.expect(tools.length).to.be.at.least(16);",
									"});"
								]
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n    \"id\": 2,\n    \"method\": \"tools/list\",\n    \"params\": {}\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{brain_url}}/messages?sessionId={{session_id}}",
							"host": ["{{brain_url}}"],
							"path": ["messages"],
							"query": [
								{
									"key": "sessionId",
